COMPUTER VISION PROJECT¶

PART-A¶

• DOMAIN: Botanical Research

• CONTEXT: University X is currently undergoing some research involving understanding the characteristics of plant and plant seedlings at various stages of growth. They already have have invested on curating sample images. They require an automation which can create a classifier capable of determining a plant's species from a photo.

• DATA DESCRIPTION: The dataset comprises of images from 12 plant species. Source: https://www.kaggle.com/c/plant-seedlings-classification/data.

• PROJECT OBJECTIVE: To create a classifier capable of determining a plant's species from a photo

def random_images(n):
    rand = np.random.randint(0,len(x),n)
    print(rand)
    plt.figure(figsize=(15,15))
    for i,j in enumerate(rand):
        plt.subplot(1,len(rand),i+1)
        plt.imshow(x[j])
        plt.title("{}".format(y[j]))
        plt.axis("off")
        plt.show()

In [33]:
#creating CNN model
model = Sequential()

#1st convolution layer
model.add(BatchNormalization(input_shape = (128,128,3)))
model.add(Convolution2D(filters=32,kernel_size=(3,3),activation='relu',input_shape=(128,128,3)))
#maxpooling
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))

#adding flatten
model.add(Flatten())

#adding ann layer
model.add(Dense(units=32,activation='relu'))
#final layer
model.add(Dense(units=12,activation='softmax'))

In [38]:
def loss_plot(history):
    plt.plot(history.history['loss'])
    plt.plot(history.history['val_loss'])
    plt.title('Model Loss')
    plt.ylabel('loss')
    plt.xlabel('epoch')
    plt.legend(['training','validation'],loc='best')
    plt.show()
def accuracy_plot(history):
    plt.plot(history.history['accuracy'])
    plt.plot(history.history['val_accuracy'])
    plt.title('Model accuracy')
    plt.ylabel('Accuracy')
    plt.xlabel('epoch')
    plt.legend(['training','validation'],loc='best')
    plt.show()

model_final = Sequential()

model_final.add(BatchNormalization(input_shape=(128,128,3)))

model_final.add(Conv2D(filters=32,kernel_size=(3,3),activation='relu',padding='valid',input_shape=(128,128,3),kernel_initializer = 'he_normal',kernel_regularizer='l2'))
model_final.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))

model_final.add(Conv2D(filters=64,kernel_size=(3,3),activation='relu',padding='valid',kernel_initializer = 'he_normal',kernel_regularizer='l2'))
model_final.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))

model_final.add(Conv2D(filters=128,kernel_size=(3,3),activation='relu',padding='valid'))
model_final.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))

model_final.add(Conv2D(filters=256,kernel_size=(3,3),activation='relu',padding='valid'))
model_final.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))

model_final.add(Conv2D(filters=512,kernel_size=(3,3),activation='relu',padding='valid'))
model_final.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))

model_final.add(Flatten())

model_final.add(Dropout(0.8))

model_final.add(Dense(128,activation='relu'))

model_final.add(Dropout(0.2))

model_final.add(Dense(units=12,activation='softmax'))
            
model_final.compile(loss=tf.keras.losses.categorical_crossentropy,optimizer = 'adam',metrics=['accuracy'])

model_final.summary()

#CNN Model

model = Sequential()

#input layer with Batchnormalization
model.add(BatchNormalization(input_shape=(128,128,3,)))

#1st convolution layer
model.add(Conv2D(48,kernel_size=(3,3),padding='valid',activation='relu',input_shape=(128,128,3),kernel_initializer = 'he_normal',kernel_regularizer = 'l2'))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))

#batchnormalization
model.add(BatchNormalization())

#2nd convolution layer
model.add(Conv2D(64,kernel_size=(3,3),padding='valid',activation='relu',kernel_initializer = 'he_normal',kernel_regularizer = 'l2'))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))

model.add(BatchNormalization())

#3rd convolution layer
model.add(Conv2D(128,kernel_size=(3,3),padding='valid',activation='relu',kernel_initializer = 'he_normal'))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))

model.add(BatchNormalization())

#4th convolution layer
model.add(Conv2D(64,kernel_size=(3,3),padding='valid',activation='relu',kernel_initializer = 'he_normal'))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))

model.add(BatchNormalization())

#5th convolution layer
model.add(Conv2D(128,kernel_size=(3,3),padding='valid',activation='relu',kernel_initializer = 'he_normal'))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))

model.add(BatchNormalization())

#adding global maxpool layer
model.add(GlobalMaxPool2D())

#flatten layer
model.add(Flatten())

#adding dropout layer to avoid overfitting
model.add(Dropout(0.8))
model.add(Dense(756,activation='relu',kernel_initializer = 'he_normal'))
model.add(Dropout(0.2))

#output layer
model.add(Dense(17,activation='softmax'))

#compile the model
model.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy',optimizer = 'adam', metrics = ['accuracy'])

hist = model.fit(x_train,y_train_cat,validation_split = 0.2,epochs=75)
